Awesome daily special.  It came with two sides and a drink.  It's worth checking out whenever you're craving meat.  It has a fair portion size and pretty quick service.  It's decor does not feel like they're a barbecue joint, but it's reasonable price help makes it more accessible.

My family was greeted warmly from the moment we stepped into the restaurant.  Then we were told to order at the beginning of the line  which was at the far end across the entrance area.  The gentleman who assisted us is the pit-master, Mr. Louise. He was friendly and gladly offered us advise when I asked what was good to try as it was our first time at that location .  Although,   my family have had Dickey' s a few times when  we visited Dallas. We had the 2 for $24 deal which includes 2 platters of 2 meats,  2 sides and a bread. It was a GREAT offer.  We all loved the sliced brisket and pulled pork. The smoked Turkey and ribs were tender and juicy too. We loved the collard greens,  barbecue beans and fried  okra.  The coleslaw was good but a tad sweet to our liking.  Least favorite side was Mac and cheese. All in all we will definitely be back as it was a very reasonably priced BBQ restaurant with their promotion.  Tips: Request for the spicy barbecue sauce by the counter.  It goes well with the meats.

You wanna talk about good style southern food in the heart of Brooklyn. Brothers and sister you gotta try Dickeys then. From the moment you walk in its transports you to southern hospitality, my rootz so I know. The smell is so powerful the smoke alarm can't even recognize good taste in the air.  Its amazing thats just the feeling you get when you walk in. But, when you walk in you are immediately introduced to a staff that is beyond awesome. Friendly, personable and eager to please. You don't find that much up here but trust me, you will at Dickeys.  The food will knock your socks off. Its like a you're at Food Network Bbq square off, yes I just went there. You try samples that fit you. Hey, they do good stuff, cooking, here and I'm happy to be able to do this review. The ribs, pulled pork, brisket and then you have sides. Simply put the Mac and Cheese. Just grandma would make every Sunday. But, so much better, don't tell grandma.  If you're visiting and want a sense of home or live here and want a sense of authentic, in my opinion, southern food then Dickeys is my first recommendation and more than likely the only.  Enjoy guys!  Mattie J!

Delicious! When the owner heard we had never been there before, he gave us samples of some of the meats. The brisket and pulled pork were my favorite. Juicy, flavorful, and delicious. Will definitely be going back again.
